This paper discusses the use of stochastic models to predict popularity of content in social media, which involves analyzing user behavior and social dynamics. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including social networks (cs.SI), data mining (cs.SD), cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SOC), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
